{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":601,"text":"I'm an artist and I cut books."},{"time":2610,"text":"This is one of my first book works."},{"time":4316,"text":"It's called \"Alternate\nRoute to Knowledge.\""},{"time":6340,"text":"I wanted to create a stack of books so\nthat somebody could come into the gallery"},{"time":10132,"text":"and think they're just looking\nat a regular stack of books,"},{"time":12952,"text":"but then as they got closer they would\nsee this rough hole carved into it,"},{"time":16441,"text":"and wonder what was happening,\nwonder why,"},{"time":18417,"text":"and think about the material of the book."},{"time":20453,"text":"So I'm interested in the texture,"},{"time":22543,"text":"but I'm more interested in the text\nand the images that we find within books."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27623,"text":"In most of my work, what I do is I seal\nthe edges of a book with a thick varnish"},{"time":31524,"text":"so it's creating sort of a skin\non the outside of the book"},{"time":34334,"text":"so it becomes a solid material,\nbut then the pages inside are still loose,"},{"time":38202,"text":"and then I carve\ninto the surface of the book,"},{"time":40352,"text":"and I'm not moving or adding anything."},{"time":42883,"text":"I'm just carving around\nwhatever I find interesting."},{"time":45762,"text":"So everything you see\nwithin the finished piece"},{"time":48223,"text":"is exactly where it was\nin the book before I began."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52666,"text":"I think of my work as sort of\na remix, in a way,"},{"time":55014,"text":"because I'm working with\nsomebody else's material"},{"time":57345,"text":"in the same way that a D.J. might be\nworking with somebody else's music."},{"time":60973,"text":"This was a book of Raphael paintings,\nthe Renaissance artist,"},{"time":64918,"text":"and by taking his work\nand remixing it, carving into it,"},{"time":69353,"text":"I'm sort of making it into something\nthat's more new and more contemporary."},{"time":73915,"text":"I'm thinking also about breaking out\nof the box of the traditional book"},{"time":77781,"text":"and pushing that linear format,"},{"time":79917,"text":"and try to push the structure\nof the book itself"},{"time":83900,"text":"so that the book can become\nfully sculptural."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89303,"text":"I'm using clamps and ropes\nand all sorts of materials, weights,"},{"time":93068,"text":"in order to hold things \nin place before I varnish"},{"time":96040,"text":"so that I can push the form \nbefore I begin,"},{"time":98600,"text":"so that something like this\ncan become a piece like this,"},{"time":103242,"text":"which is just made\nfrom a single dictionary."},{"time":106130,"text":"Or something like this\ncan become a piece like this."},{"time":114768,"text":"Or something like this,"},{"time":116244,"text":"which who knows what that's going to be\nor why that's in my studio,"},{"time":120255,"text":"will become a piece like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124997,"text":"So I think one of the reasons\npeople are disturbed by destroying books,"},{"time":128685,"text":"people don't want to rip books"},{"time":130228,"text":"and nobody really wants\nto throw away a book,"},{"time":132359,"text":"is that we think about books\nas living things,"},{"time":134552,"text":"we think about them as a body,"},{"time":136223,"text":"and they're created\nto relate to our body, as far as scale,"},{"time":139313,"text":"but they also have the potential\nto continue to grow"},{"time":141741,"text":"and to continue to become new things."},{"time":143731,"text":"So books really are alive."},{"time":146458,"text":"So I think of the book as a body,"},{"time":148988,"text":"and I think of the book as a technology."},{"time":151692,"text":"I think of the book as a tool."},{"time":156111,"text":"And I also think of the book as a machine."},{"time":160435,"text":"I also think of the book as a landscape."},{"time":162809,"text":"This is a full set of encyclopedias\nthat's been connected and sanded together,"},{"time":167081,"text":"and as I carve through it,"},{"time":169334,"text":"I'm deciding what I want to choose."},{"time":171275,"text":"So with encyclopedias,\nI could have chosen anything,"},{"time":173863,"text":"but I specifically chose\nimages of landscapes."},{"time":178030,"text":"And with the material itself,\nI'm using sandpaper"},{"time":180966,"text":"and sanding the edges\nso not only the images suggest landscape,"},{"time":184658,"text":"but the material itself\nsuggests a landscape as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189456,"text":"So one of the things I do\nis when I'm carving through the book,"},{"time":192889,"text":"I'm thinking about images,\nbut I'm also thinking about text,"},{"time":196570,"text":"and I think about them\nin a very similar way,"},{"time":198775,"text":"because what's interesting\nis that when we're reading text,"},{"time":201647,"text":"when we're reading a book,"},{"time":203146,"text":"it puts images in our head,"},{"time":204615,"text":"so we're sort of filling that piece."},{"time":206638,"text":"We're sort of creating images\nwhen we're reading text,"},{"time":210039,"text":"and when we're looking at an image,\nwe actually use language"},{"time":212916,"text":"in order to understand\nwhat we're looking at."},{"time":215632,"text":"So there's sort of\na yin-yang that happens,"},{"time":217861,"text":"sort of a flip flop."},{"time":219138,"text":"So I'm creating a piece\nthat the viewer is completing themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225477,"text":"And I think of my work\nas almost an archaeology."},{"time":228960,"text":"I'm excavating and I'm trying\nto maximize the potential"},{"time":231979,"text":"and discover as much as I possibly can"},{"time":234068,"text":"and exposing it within my own work."},{"time":238219,"text":"But at the same time,"},{"time":239896,"text":"I'm thinking about this idea of erasure,"},{"time":241870,"text":"and what's happening now that most\nof our information is intangible,"},{"time":246351,"text":"and this idea of loss,"},{"time":249393,"text":"and this idea that not only is the format\nconstantly shifting within computers,"},{"time":253711,"text":"but the information itself,"},{"time":256033,"text":"now that we don't have a physical backup,"},{"time":258262,"text":"has to be constantly updated\nin order to not lose it."},{"time":263843,"text":"And I have several dictionaries\nin my own studio,"},{"time":266623,"text":"and I do use a computer every day,"},{"time":269140,"text":"and if I need to look up a word,\nI'll go on the computer,"},{"time":271933,"text":"because I can go directly\nand instantly to what I'm looking up."},{"time":275259,"text":"I think that the book was never really"},{"time":277209,"text":"the right format\nfor nonlinear information,"},{"time":280204,"text":"which is why we're seeing reference books"},{"time":282278,"text":"becoming the first to be \nendangered or extinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289743,"text":"So I don't think that the book\nwill ever really die."},{"time":292510,"text":"People think that now that we have\ndigital technology,"},{"time":296806,"text":"the book is going to die,"},{"time":298178,"text":"and we are seeing things shifting\nand things evolving."},{"time":301381,"text":"I think that the book will evolve,"},{"time":303505,"text":"and just like people said\npainting would die"},{"time":306767,"text":"when photography and printmaking\nbecame everyday materials,"},{"time":311167,"text":"but what it really allowed painting to do"},{"time":313154,"text":"was it allowed painting\nto quit its day job."},{"time":315706,"text":"It allowed painting to not have to have\nthat everyday chore of telling the story,"},{"time":322022,"text":"and painting became free\nand was allowed to tell its own story,"},{"time":325435,"text":"and that's when we saw Modernism emerge,"},{"time":327512,"text":"and we saw painting\ngo into different branches."},{"time":329754,"text":"And I think that's what's\nhappening with books now,"},{"time":332238,"text":"now that most of our technology,\nmost of our information,"},{"time":334933,"text":"most of our personal and cultural \nrecords are in digital form,"},{"time":339127,"text":"I think it's really allowing the book\nto become something new."},{"time":342079,"text":"So I think it's a very exciting time\nfor an artist like me,"},{"time":344869,"text":"and it's very exciting to see what\nwill happen with the book in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348439,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349768,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}